description:
Issue 1-10 of 'Cannon &amp; Cannon's Double Barrel'
Top Shelf Productions, 2012-2013, a whole lotta pages (see below)
Written and Illustrated by Kevin Cannon, Zander Cannon, Tim Sievert

Each issue of 'Double Barrel' contains a chapter of two ongoing series (get it, &quot;double barrel&quot;, by two Cannons no less) by Kevin Cannon and Zander Cannon (who are not actually related). 

Zander got his start in comics on The Tick spin-off 'Chainsaw Vigilante' and did quite a bit of other work in &quot;The City&quot; as well. You can find that work in the recently uploaded 'The Tick' torrent. His comic book work since then is quite extensive. You can read more about it right here... &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zander_Cannon&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zander_Cannon&lt;/a&gt;

Zander's ongoing title in 'Double Barrel' is 'Heck', of which a collected volume was printed by Top Shelf Productions in June, 2013.

Kevin Cannon has an equally impressive resume, including writing the sequel to Alan Moore's 'Top Ten' with Zander and releasing his own gooder than good book, 'Far Arden'. You can read more about Kevin's work right here... &lt;a href=&quot;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Cannon&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kevin_Cannon&lt;/a&gt;

Kevin's ongoing title in 'Double Barrel' is 'Crater XV', the sequel to 'Far Arden', of which a collected volume was printed by Top Shelf Productions in June, 2013.

Each issue also has several backup stories and features, including Zander's 'True Tales of Jin (age 4)', Kevin's 'Penny from the Front', other one-off and guest collaboration stories, and 'How to...' articles in relation to comic books, graphic novels, storytelling, etc.

Starting with Issue 9, Cannon &amp; Cannon were joined by Tim Sievert, the creator, author and artist behind 'That Salty Air'. &lt;a href=&quot;
http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/8676143/That_Salty_Air_(2012)_(digital-Empire)&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/8676143/That_Salty_Air_(2012)_(digital-Empire)&lt;/a&gt;

Tim is contributing a third ongoing story titled, 'The Clandestinauts'.

Issue 1 - 122 pages, Issue 2 - 100 pages, Issue 3 - 116 pages, Issue 4 - 81 pages, Issue 5 - 114 pages, Issue 6 - 102 pages, Issue 7 - 88 pages, Issue 8 - 101 pages, Issue 9 - 140 pages, Issue 10 - 138 pages
